======================================================================
ANALYSIS 2: PAIR-COVERAGE -> DISJOINTNESS -> H
======================================================================

Pair-coverage variance analysis:

  H=175: sum_lam=42, sum_lam2=98, var_lam=0.6667, disj=14
    lambda dist: {1: 7, 2: 7, 3: 7}
    overlap-2 from lambda = sum C(lam,2) = 28
    ov0=14, ov1=49, ov2=28
    Check: ov0+ov1+ov2 = 91

FORMULA: disj = sum_edges C(lambda_e, 2) - 14
         = sum_edges lambda_e*(lambda_e-1)/2 - 14
         = (sum lambda_e^2 - sum lambda_e)/2 - 14
         = (sum_lam2 - 42)/2 - 14
         = sum_lam2/2 - 35
  H=175: sum_lam2=98, disj_pred=14, disj_actual=14, match=YES

======================================================================
ANALYSIS 3: H AS A FUNCTION OF LAMBDA VARIANCE
======================================================================
Computing directly:
  H=189 (BIBD): var_lam=0, H = 189
  H=171: sum_lam2=90, var_lam=0.285714 = 6/21
    H predicted = 171.00
  H=175: sum_lam2=98, var_lam=0.666667 = 14/21
    H predicted = 175.00

  Parabola vertex: var_lam = 3/7 = 0.428571
  H at vertex = 168.75

  H(disj) = disj^2 - 23*disj + 301
  Minimum at disj = 23/2 = 11.5
  H_min = 168.75
  Paley (disj=7) is FARTHEST from minimum -> HIGHEST H
  H=171 (disj=10) and H=175 (disj=14) bracket the minimum

